{
  "texts": [
    "DS compares the area of segmented regions of the generated synthetic images and real ground truth images with the total area of both regions (Ghaffari et al. 2019).",
    "The formula for DS is calculated using Eq. 20:",
    "In Eq. 20 reported in Ghaffari et al. (2019), Y pred indicates the ground truth, Y pred indicates the predicting label and is a small number used for avoiding division by zero.",
    "Perfect segmentation is indicated by the DS of 1.0.",
    "In GANs, classification metrics such as recall and precision are also used to evaluate the quality and diversity of synthetic images (Borji 2019)."
  ]
}